# Changelog rule

When you make **new changes** to the codebase or **add new features**:

1. **Update `docs/CHANGELOG.md`** with the changes.
2. Add entries under the appropriate section: `### Added`, `### Changed`, `### Fixed`, or `### Removed`.
3. Put new entries at the **top** of the relevant section (most recent first).
4. Write a short, clear line per change (e.g. "Hero: subheading set to X", "New component Y for Z").

Do this as part of the same task—don’t leave the changelog for later.
